Service: zimbraMail
Namespace: "urn:zimbraMail"
Sync SOAP Command

Sync

  • Ssync on other mailbox is done via specifying target account in SOAP header
  • If we're delta syncing on another user's mailbox and any folders have changed:
    • If there are now no visible folders, you'll get an empty <folder/> element
    • If there are any visible folders, you'll get the full visible folder hierarchy
  • If a {root-folder-id} other than the mailbox root (folder 1) is requested or if not all folders are visible when syncing to another user's mailbox, all changed items in other folders are presented as deletes
  • If the response is a mail.MUST_RESYNC fault, client has fallen too far out of date and must re-initial sync

Authorization token required true
Admin Authorization token required false

SyncRequest

    <SyncRequest [token="{sync-token}"] [calCutoff="{earliest-calendar-date} (Long)"] [l="{root-folder-id}"]
                    [typed="{break-down-deletes-by-item-type} (0|1)"] /> ## SyncRequest

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <SyncRequest> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description
@token Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Token - not provided for initial sync
@calCutoff Optional (0 or 1) Type:Long
Earliest Calendar date. If present, omit all appointments and tasks that don't have a recurrence ending after that time (specified in ms)
@l Optional (0 or 1) Type:String
Root folder ID. If present, we start sync there rather than at folder 11
@typed Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
If specified and set, deletes are also broken down by item type
